        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "briefDescription": "Under this scheme, financial assistance is provided to elderly people aged 60 years and above living Below the Poverty Line (BPL) to support them in living a respectful life.",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Indira Gandhi National Old Age Pension Scheme&amp;quot; is implemented by the Social Welfare Department, Government of Chhattisgarh. Under this scheme, financial assistance is provided to elderly people aged 60 years and above living Below the Poverty Line (BPL) to support them in living a respectful life. This scheme is centrally sponsored.\n",
        "benefits_md": "Eligible beneficiaries under this scheme will receive monthly financial assistance as follows:\n\n  - **Beneficiaries aged 60 to 79 years:**  ₹500/- per month (Central contribution: ₹200/-, State contribution: ₹300/-).  - **Beneficiaries aged 80 years or above:** ₹650/- per month (Central contribution: ₹500/-, State contribution: ₹150/-).\n",
        "exclusions_md": "",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
